Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
create_interposer_route_block(25.10)      create_interposer_route_block(25.10)

Name
       create_interposer_route_block - Creates the master block

Syntax
        create_interposer_route_block

       [-help]

       -cell <cell_name>

       -dir <dir_name>

       -inst  <master_name>[{-box  {<x1  y1  x2  y2>} | -polygon {<x1 y1 x2 y2
       ...>} | -rects {{<lx1 ly1 ux1 uy1>} {<lx2 ly2 ux2 uy2>}...}}]

       Creates the master block. It transforms the routed domain to  a  master
       partition block that enrolls all the special routes.

       Note:  If  the  design  does  not  have  a  routing pattern that can be
       treated as a master  block,  the  functionality  of  the  create_inter-
       poser_route_block  command  can  be replaced by loading the LEF file of
       the master partition that has the same routing pattern using the loadL-
       efFile command. After this, the add_interposer_route_block command  can
       be used directly.

       Note:  The  create_interposer_route_block command reports the number of
       physical cells and logical cells in the specified block area.

Parameters
       -box {<x1 y1 x2 y2>}
              Specifies the master block's bounding box.

              Note: The snapping grid of the created block  honors  the  setF-
              PlanMode -snapBlockGrid command settings.

              Data_type: box, optional

       -cell <cell_name>
              Specifies the master cell name.

              Data_type: string, required

       -dir <dir_name>
              Specifies the directory name that will contain the partition in-
              formation  and  files.  The tool creates the directory and saves
              the information and files for the top and master block partition
              automatically after the create_interposer_route_block command is
              used.

              Data_type: string, required

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information  for  each  create_interposer_route_block parameter.
              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man create_interposer_route_block

       -inst <master_name>
              Specifies the master block name.

              Note: The default orientation of the created master block is R0.

              Data_type: string, required

       -polygon {<x1 y1 x2 y2 ...>}
              Specifies the corner coordinates of the rectilinear block.

              Note: Only rectilinear polygons are supported.

              Data_type: polygon, optional

       -rects {{<lx1 ly1 ux1 uy1>} {<lx2 ly2 ux2 uy2>}...}
              Specifies one or more rectangles that are  used  to  create  one
              shape. The low left corner coordinate and the upper right corner
              coordinate of each rectangle should be specified.

              Data_type: box_list, optional

Examples
              * The following command transforms the routed domain to a master
                partition block.

                create_interposer_route_block   -cell   cell_name  -inst  mas-
                ter_block -box {llx lly urx ury} -dir PTN

